  # 3.JWT
  - JWT JSON WEB TOKEN ARE STATELESS SOLUTION FOR AUTHENTICATION SO THERE IS NO NEED TO STORE ANY SESSION STATE IN SERVER 
  - which is perfect for the restfull api .Restfull should be stateless
  - Alternative is to just store the user data using the session 
  
  ![jwt.png](:storage/38c4d807-594c-4c60-82d4-3da1c3de91e7/4620fe3c.png)![howjwtlookslike.png](:storage/38c4d807-594c-4c60-82d4-3da1c3de91e7/40595b66.png)!
  > Once a server recieves a JWT to grant access to protected route it needs to be verified, in order to determine if the user really is who he claimed to be.
  
